ials brought the broadcast model of radio and television to the big screen and thereby introduced models of serial storytelling that informed popular culture even beyond the serial's demise.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aFilm serialsxHistory. 4aFilm, Media, and Communication. 7aART / Film & Video.2bisacsh  aFilm Serials, Seriality, Film History, Media History, Modernity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2016-2018z978311066731808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060672040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048537808?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048537808zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048537808/original  a978-3-11-060672-0 Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-066731-8 AUP eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA